message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Paraguay, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you enjoy walking, you can simply walk to the grocery store. It will take you approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km on foot.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, cycling can be a convenient and quick way to reach the grocery store. It will take you around 3-5 minutes to cover the 1km distance, depending on your speed.

3. Public Transportation: Paraguay has a public transportation system, including buses and taxis. You can check if there is a bus route that passes near your location and takes you to the grocery store. Alternatively, you can hail a taxi or use ride-sharing services like Uber or Cabify for a more comfortable and direct journey.

4. Driving: If you have access to a car or can rent one, driving to the grocery store is another option. It will be a short drive of around 2-3 minutes, depending on traffic conditions.

Consider the available options based on your preferences, convenience, and the resources at your disposal.
